---
description: API documentation — Swagger/OpenAPI decoration conventions for every NestJS endpoint
globs: ["apps/api/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Reference: `ARCHITECTURE.md` Part 1, "API documentation: Swagger/OpenAPI."
The exported OpenAPI JSON (`/api/docs-json`) is the actual contract — it's
what frontend types are generated from (`openapi-typescript` →
`apps/web/src/lib/shared/api/generated-types.ts`). Undecorated or
partially decorated endpoints silently break that pipeline, so this isn't
optional polish.

- **Every controller gets `@ApiTags(<boundedContext>)`** — one tag per
  module, matching its folder name.

- **Every controller method gets `@ApiOperation({ summary, description })`
  and `@ApiResponse()` for each real response shape**, success and error.
  Don't ship an endpoint with no `@ApiOperation`.

- **Every request/response DTO is a decorated class** —
  `@ApiProperty()`/`@ApiPropertyOptional()` on every field. Never a plain
  `interface` or an inferred return type at a controller boundary; Swagger
  can't generate a schema from either, and a missing schema silently
  produces a wrong/empty type on the frontend side of the generated-types
  pipeline.

- **State the Propose/Confirm split in the operation description, not just
  the method name.** E.g. `proposeOutcome`'s description: "Returns a
  candidate only — never writes. Call confirmOutcome to persist." Anyone
  (human or agent) integrating against this endpoint should be able to
  tell from the docs alone that it doesn't write.

- **State guard/scope requirements in the operation description.**
  `@UseGuards(SectionSubjectWriteGuard)` doesn't surface in the generated
  schema — write it in words: which `teacher_sections` grain is required
  to call this endpoint successfully.

- **A module isn't done until its controller + DTOs are fully decorated.**
  Treat this the same as a missing mapper-guard test or missing RLS
  policy — a PR gap to flag, not a follow-up ticket.

- **Frontend code must import types from `generated-types.ts`, never
  redeclare a backend response shape by hand** — that's the other half of
  this contract; see `.cursor/rules/60-frontend-architecture.mdc` rule 7.
